CDC's new toolkit can help you continue to help people understand the vaccines & address questions & concerns.

.@CDCGov encourages everyone to get a #COVID19 vaccine when available. Pfizer-BioNTech and Moderna vaccines are being administered. Patients w/appointments for J&J vaccine can work with vaccination providers to reschedule to get a different shot. More: https://t.co/nSBV5jiSFg https://t.co/s0oPARgmuI

Community partners working together can help promote vaccine confidence. Learn how @CDCgov and @JohnsHopkins partnered with religious leaders in the city’s African American community to help build trust and understanding about #COVID19 vaccination: https://t.co/2Tl5d7B9gf

Properly storing and transporting vaccines is a critical part of the #COVID19 vaccination effort. In this 17-minute video, earn #CE while you review best practices for transportation and storage of #COVID19 vaccines. See https://t.co/gAG7xbmjhJ https://t.co/0Ad7TlckED

If you are working at a #COVID19 vaccination site, protect yourself from needlestick injuries while administering vaccines or helping at the site. 

Learn more: https://t.co/TsTmeFeNyQ https://t.co/0OrukP8DI3

HCPs, see the #COVID19 Vaccine Quick Reference Guide for a table comparing vaccine storage, handling, and administration requirements for all currently authorized vaccines in the U.S. View the PDF: https://t.co/LPuneqJTFw https://t.co/CLBV2vtNu1

#HCPs: @CDCgov offers a series of 15- to 20-minute webinars specific to #COVID19 vaccination. Continuing education is offered for each of the 4 modules currently available. Learn more at https://t.co/dklhXiYydf https://t.co/JgDQl83Ol6

A new, on-demand webinar from @CDCgov offers free #CE. In this 20-minute video primer for healthcare workers, participants can review how to prevent common #COVID19 vaccine administration errors. Access the webinar at https://t.co/V9fE1BFzlx https://t.co/VRYfCeL8sf

#COVID19 vaccines will keep you from getting COVID-19. 
As of April 5, more than 107 million people in the United States had received at least one dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Of those, more than 62 million are fully vaccinated. 

More data: https://t.co/FHGplToHFM https://t.co/n7Aij95TY2

More than 100 million people have received at least 1 dose of a #COVID19 vaccine. My thanks to the thousands of healthcare and government personnel, scientists, community leaders, volunteers, and everyone else across the country who made this possible.
#VaccinesWork https://t.co/0Dfzu4ihei
The U.S. hits a milestone today: 100+ MILLION PEOPLE HAVE RECEIVED COVID-19 VACCINES

HCPs: As #COVID19 vaccines continue to roll out, states are creating programs specific to their populations’ needs. Learn about a unique approach to distributing COVID-19 vaccines and educating communities in Connecticut: https://t.co/hO38bJWVSy https://t.co/HmSccbrnOT

Vaccination Providers: CDC’s pregnancy registry uses v-safe, @CDCgov after-vaccination health checker, to learn more about #COVID19 vaccination during pregnancy. Encourage pregnant vaccine recipients to participate if someone from the registry calls. See  https://t.co/HcFKMbKZGK https://t.co/7inSu7gA2r
